<item>
            <title>[SHIRO-591] Basic Auth Filter permissive mode does NOT work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-591</link>
                <project id="12310950" key="SHIRO">Shiro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SHIRO-200&quot; title=&quot;Add ability to configure basic authentication for specific HTTP methods &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SHIRO-200&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SHIRO-200&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; assumed all filter options were http methods, for example:&lt;/p&gt;
{authcBasic[POST, GET]}

&lt;p&gt;However, the &apos;permissive&apos; option is also valid, which instructs the filter to check for authentication, but NOT require it:&lt;/p&gt;
{authcBasic[permissive]}
&lt;p&gt;Or the two combine in something like:&lt;br/&gt;
authcBasic&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;permissive,POST, GET&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
