                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16218145" author="marcode" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2017 05:48:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I currently try to use authcBasic&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;permissive&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; mode with 1.4.0. If I set to non permissive, every request is checked, if i set permissive no request is checked for basic auth. To me it seems that there is still some kind of bug in there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16218659" author="bdemers" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2017 13:52:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marcode&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marcode&quot;&gt;marcode&lt;/a&gt;  even if the header is present?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16219400" author="marcode" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2017 19:48:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brian I just found out that the problem was on my site! I passed the credentials in a format which was not picked up in authcBasic&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;permissive&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; but worked in authcBasic! Passing it differently now works!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16219418" author="bdemers" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2017 19:57:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great! was it encoded differently?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16219427" author="marcode" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2017 20:03:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the sake of reference &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does NOT work&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HttpAuthenticationFeature feature = HttpAuthenticationFeature.universalBuilder()&lt;br/&gt;
			.credentials(&quot;esadmin&quot;, AllTestsSuite.ADMIN_TEST_PASSWORD).build();&lt;br/&gt;
client.register(feature)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;does work&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HttpAuthenticationFeature feature = HttpAuthenticationFeature.basic(&quot;esadmin&quot;, AllTestsSuite.ADMIN_TEST_PASSWORD);&lt;br/&gt;
		final Client client = ClientBuilder.newClient();&lt;br/&gt;
		client.register(feature);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;using OSGI Jax RS consumer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
